cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.DS

The paper presents a novel metaheuristic optimization algorithm inspired by quantum mechanics and chaos theory. It also includes a comparative analysis with other nature-inspired approaches and discusses convergence issues. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The algorithm also involves networked agents and draws upon control theory concepts, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control). The performance analysis and convergence issues discussed in the paper may also relate to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
